item.title: 11 Celebrity Lookalikes Riding Public Transportation
item.dc:creator: Benny Bernardo
item.description:
With all the different kinds of people that you bump into during your daily commute, you’re bound to find a couple of strangers who look familiar. Some of them might look like someone you personally know, and others might just happen to look like famous people. And when it’s the latter, well, it’s bound to make […]

The post 11 Celebrity Lookalikes Riding Public Transportation appeared first on EgoTV.
item.content:encoded:
With all the different kinds of people that you bump into during your daily commute, you’re bound to find a couple of strangers who look familiar. Some of them might look like someone you personally know, and others might just happen to look like famous people. And when it’s the latter, well, it’s bound to make your heart jump a bit, because what if it’s really them?! Then again, the odds are pretty slim because celebrities don’t usually ride the bus or the metro (unless they’re Keanu Reeves).

Below are some snapshots of some of those strangers who look almost exactly like famous celebrities. We swear, the resemblances are uncanny! We even had to check if some of them were really strangers. With the exception of the dude who looks like Wolverine, these are really spot on. We have to thank all the people who contributed these amazing “paparazzi” shots for all the Internet to see!

1. Bob Marley

2. Morgan Freeman

3. Albert Einstein

4. Vin Diesel

5. Tom “Loki” Hiddleston

6. Hugh Jackma / Wolverine

7. Dora the Explorer

8. Stan Lee

9. Jack Nicholson

10. Carlos Santana

11. Vin Diesel

The post 11 Celebrity Lookalikes Riding Public Transportation appeared first on EgoTV.

item.title: 7 Adorable Food Puns You Can Send To Your Special Someone
item.dc:creator: Benny Bernardo
item.description:
It’s nowhere near Valentine’s Day (unless you can time travel back to a couple of weeks ago) but sweet messages for lovers are always in season. You can get those in Hallmark cards or make up your own, then again they can be a little redundant or too cheesy. The Internet has a lot of […]

The post 7 Adorable Food Puns You Can Send To Your Special Someone appeared first on EgoTV.
item.content:encoded:
It’s nowhere near Valentine’s Day (unless you can time travel back to a couple of weeks ago) but sweet messages for lovers are always in season. You can get those in Hallmark cards or make up your own, then again they can be a little redundant or too cheesy. The Internet has a lot of these, but if you’re like me, you’ll probably want something a little more creative and funny at the same time. After all, with the release of endorphins coming along with it, your partner is bound to have a nice smile on his or her face.

So if you want something a little “new” and cute for your snugglebunny, here are a couple of cute messages that includes funny food puns. Just read them, at least two of them will tickle you funny–in a good way! Our personal favorite is the one with the pizza. Let us know which one’s yours, in the comments area below!

The post 7 Adorable Food Puns You Can Send To Your Special Someone appeared first on EgoTV.

The post 22 Creative And Punny Restaurant Names appeared first on EgoTV.
item.content:encoded:
With restaurant competition getting very tight around the world where new ones keep popping up, there’s an incredible need for good marketing. What I learned about making your service sell is to, first and foremost, give it a catchy name that will stick with consumers and passersby. And for a new restaurant, you know that’s pretty much a must.

Thankfully for these businesses, they’ve got clever owners who came up with “punny” and appropriately-themed restaurant names that one wouldn’t forget. Heck, I wish I could check these out myself! Now, if only the food were good too. If it ain’t, well at least these restaurants sure got crowds of first-timers coming in just for their quirky, familiar names!

item.content:encoded:
Weddings are pretty serious gigs. And if you’re getting married, you want to make sure everything goes perfectly well–from the event program, your entourage, the food, decor, to the documentation. After all, you want to remember this moment in the next 50 or so years and have the same smile planted on your face.

But what if something goes wrong? Specifically, what if you wanted to look back and saw photos that you can never retake? Just check out these wedding photos that we’ll bet the married couple fought about a couple of times–that is, if they’re still together after everything that we’ve seen here! And can we say, if you want to avoid any of these, make sure you have a good photographer and to always be conscious of your actions because the cameras are everywhere! You’ve been warned.

item.content:encoded:
Wild animals are truly amazing, more so because of the fact that we rarely see them in our lifetime. Thankfully, many passionate wildlife photographers have spent a lot of their time (not to mention risked their lives) to take incredible photos of wildlife and its inhabitants. They’re nothing short of remarkable!

Take a look at just some of the photos that have been made available on the Internet. Prepare to see animals at their most honest forms–hungry and wild. These photographers went in close enough and clicked fast enough to make it real-life, too. They’re pretty unbelievable!
